        <p>NRG ENERGY INC., Minneapolis, a power-plant operator that first sold shares to the public in May, agreed to buy three electrical-generating assets from Sierra Pacific Resources, Reno, Nev., a utility holding company, for $273.3 million.</p>
        <p>DOW CHEMICAL CO., Midland, Mich., said it would buy the biotechnology services unit of the privately held Collaborative Group to expand into the growing market for biopharmaceutical drugs. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
